  "text": "In recent years, cell therapy, mainly using autologous bone marrow stromal cells (BMSCs), is configured as a hope for patients suffering neurological sequelae due to spinal cord injury (SCI) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Although a paracrine effect, by releasing neurotrophic factors by transplanted stem cells is considered as the main cause of improvement, it is difficult to answer the multiple questions posed by the efficacy of these techniques.",
